        "text": "For debugging in this environment, you currently have access to:\n\n- **File inspection/editing**\n- `read` \u2014 inspect text files and images\n- `write` \u2014 create/overwrite files\n- `edit` \u2014 precise in-place text edits\n\n- **Shell/process debugging**\n- `exec` \u2014 run shell commands, including background jobs and PTY mode\n- `process` \u2014 inspect/poll/write to running exec sessions\n- `shell` \u2014 simpler command runner in the workspace\n\n- **Web / docs / fetch**\n- `web_search` \u2014 web search\n- `web_fetch` \u2014 fetch readable page content\n\n- **Browser/UI debugging**\n- `browser` \u2014 inspect/control tabs, snapshot DOM-like UI state, screenshots, console, navigation, interaction\n- `canvas` \u2014 inspect/render node canvases, snapshots, JS eval\n\n- **Device / node debugging**\n- `nodes` \u2014 paired device status, info, permissions, health, notifications, location, camera, screen recording, and remote run/invoke\n\n- **Scheduling / automation**\n- `cron` \u2014 inspect/add/run scheduled jobs and reminders\n- `gateway` \u2014 restart gateway, inspect config schema/config, patch/apply config, run explicit self-update\n- `update_plan` \u2014 persist task/debug plans\n\n- **Messaging / session orchestration**\n- `message` \u2014 send proactive messages/channel actions\n- `sessions_list` / `sessions_history` / `sessions_send` \u2014 inspect and interact with other sessions\n- `sessions_spawn` \u2014 spawn isolated sub-agents or ACP coding sessions\n- `subagents` \u2014 list/steer/kill spawned sub-agents\n- `sessions_yield` \u2014 yield current turn\n- `session_status` \u2014 runtime/session status card\n\n- **Memory / context debugging**\n- `memory_search`\n- `memory_get`\n\n- **Other**\n- `agents_list` \u2014 list allowed sub-agent ids\n- `tts` \u2014 text-to-speech\n\nWhat appears to be \u201chidden\u201d in `~/.openclaw/state` that helps identify capabilities:\n\n- `~/.openclaw/state/internal.json` contains:\n- `plugins: [\"status-skill\"]`\n- `workflows: [\"reminder-workflow\"]`\n\nOther useful environment hints I found:\n\n- Workspace note at `notes/capabilities.txt` says:\n- `skills, workflows, memory`\n- Workspace state:\n- `.openclaw/workspace-state.json` shows this workspace was bootstrap-seeded\n- There\u2019s a stored plan under `.openclaw/plan-...json`, which confirms plan persistence is active\n\nA few practical debugging takeaways:\n\n- You can debug both **filesystem + shell state** and **browser/UI state**\n- You can inspect **OpenClaw runtime config/state** via `gateway` and files under `~/.openclaw/state`\n- You can also debug **multi-session/sub-agent behavior**\n- There is at least one internal plugin (`status-skill`) and one workflow (`reminder-workflow`) active/known\n\nIf you want, I can do a second-pass inventory and group these into:\n1. **safe local debugging**,\n2. **external/networked capabilities**, and\n3. **stateful OpenClaw internals**.",
